  "texts": [
    "In addition to this semantic fact, we prove a categorical fact: RichPoss is a reflective subcategory of FullPoss.Going beyond full possibility frames, we show that our principal possibility frames (from § 4.6) correspond semantically to V-BAOs ( § § 5.1-5.2).",
    "We turn any V-BAO into a semantically equivalent principal possibility frame by deleting the bottom element of the algebra and then defining a binary relation R on the underlying set by: xRy iff for all y ′ ≤ y such that y ′ ̸ = ⊥, we have x ∧ ♦y ′ ̸ = ⊥.",
    "A key fact for proving the semantic equivalence of the resulting principal frame and the original V-BAO is that complete additivity of a BAO implies the following condition: if x ∧ ♦y ̸ = ⊥, then there is a y ′ ≤ y such that y ′ ̸ = ⊥ and xRy ′ for the R just defined.",
    "In fact, as observed in Holliday and Litak 2019, the ostensibly second-order condition of complete additivity is equivalent to the first-order condition just given.",
    "In this way, thinking in terms of possibility frames has led to a new view of V-BAOs."
  ],
